Objective
Build a system that translates spoken Bambara sentences into English, conditioned on an instruction (e.g., “translate to English”, “formal English”, “paraphrase”).
 
Inputs (X)
•	Audio waveform (Bambara speech)
•	Instruction text (task specification)
 
Outputs (y)
•	English translated text (style controlled via instruction)
 
Dataset (Bambara Speech Translation)
Fields:
•	audio → speech input
•	duration → audio length
•	text → clean transcript
•	label-v1, label-v2 → noisy transcript variants
•	translation → English translation
 
DL/NLP Type
•	Supervised sequence-to-sequence
•	Multimodal: Audio + Instruction → Text
•	Instruction-conditioned generation
 
Business / Research Metrics
•	Primary:
o	BLEU
o	chrF
o	TER
•	Secondary:
o	WER (speech recognition quality)
o	Instruction adherence accuracy
•	Optional:
o	Robustness to noisy transcripts
 
Constraints
•	Low-resource language
•	Noisy transcript variants (v1, v2)
•	Variable-length audio
•	Limited compute (GPU memory)
 
Success Criteria
•	BLEU ≥ 25 on test set
•	Instruction adherence ≥ 95%
•	Robust performance across noisy inputs
